<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-18T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="161" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860D.00/1148: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-18T13:00:00+02:00">February 18, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 18—12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>298. Source mentioned in my 297 today<note n="92" xml:id="d161fn92">The source cited in this telegram was Albin Johnson,
                                    International News Service correspondent in Finland.</note> said
                                that during conversation with Prime Minister Rangell he was closely
                                questioned as to American peace aims and what we proposed to do
                                after the war was won. Rangell stressed this [<hi rend="italic">his</hi>] interest in whether United States could exert
                                effective influence on Soviet Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">McClintock</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>